00:19:06.771 --> 00:19:08.940 position:50% align:center
[KUONJI]
Meet our signature style!

00:19:27.083 --> 00:19:28.793 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:19:28.877 --> 00:19:30.879 position:50% align:center
Ah! You guys are amazing!

00:19:30.962 --> 00:19:33.673 position:50% align:center
Love you Rui, Kakeru,
Banri, and Iori!

00:19:36.051 --> 00:19:38.094 position:50% align:center
Well, what do you
think, Kiriyama?

00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:40.722 position:50% align:center
Honestly, I'm finding
it hard to judge.

00:19:40.805 --> 00:19:42.932 position:50% align:center
There's no doubt
it was entertaining,

00:19:43.016 --> 00:19:44.851 position:50% align:center
and they're good enough
on the elements,

00:19:44.934 --> 00:19:47.145 position:50% align:center
but at the same time,
it's just so--

00:19:47.228 --> 00:19:48.938 position:50% align:center
Unexpected, and they've
taken advantage

00:19:49.022 --> 00:19:50.273 position:50% align:center
of the scoring.

00:19:50.357 --> 00:19:51.483 position:50% align:center
Fascinating.

00:19:54.235 --> 00:19:55.362 position:50% align:center
[JONOUCHI]
Wow.

00:19:55.445 --> 00:19:57.072 position:50% align:center
Guess they're really
gonna get away with it.

00:19:57.155 --> 00:19:59.240 position:50% align:center
[AKIMITSU] But what happens now?
Was that allowed?

00:19:59.324 --> 00:20:01.076 position:50% align:center
They haven't broken any rules.

00:20:01.159 --> 00:20:02.744 position:50% align:center
The fault's in how
they're written.

00:20:02.827 --> 00:20:04.871 position:50% align:center
That little sneak Kuonji
was only pretending

00:20:04.954 --> 00:20:06.581 position:50% align:center
to compete against
Himekawa when all

00:20:06.664 --> 00:20:08.583 position:50% align:center
he actually cared about
was showing everyone

00:20:08.667 --> 00:20:10.335 position:50% align:center
what his team could do.

00:20:10.418 --> 00:20:14.798 position:50% align:center
And maybe he involved Kogahara
just to stir things up. Huh.

00:20:16.508 --> 00:20:18.259 position:50% align:center
[KUBOTA] The performance
by Kuonji's team gripped

00:20:18.343 --> 00:20:21.429 position:50% align:center
the audience's heart,
there's no denying it.

00:20:21.513 --> 00:20:23.765 position:50% align:center
They obviously got high marks
on the entertainment portion

00:20:23.848 --> 00:20:24.891 position:50% align:center
of the score--

00:20:24.974 --> 00:20:27.519 position:50% align:center
in fact, they're
unrivaled on that.

00:20:27.602 --> 00:20:31.272 position:50% align:center
However, due to their
occasional technical mistakes...

00:20:37.696 --> 00:20:39.572 position:50% align:center
...they couldn't
beat Himekawa's team.

00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:41.908 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:20:41.991 --> 00:20:43.243 position:50% align:center
--[IGARASHI] We did it!
--[SHUNOBON] All right!

00:20:43.326 --> 00:20:44.452 position:50% align:center
[SATO]
Great job, Himekawa!

00:20:57.090 --> 00:20:59.300 position:50% align:center
You and your team
ended up taking third,

00:20:59.384 --> 00:21:01.511 position:50% align:center
but no one will forget your
free skate performance,

00:21:01.594 --> 00:21:03.304 position:50% align:center
which was truly phenomenal.

00:21:03.388 --> 00:21:04.931 position:50% align:center
My personal favorite!

00:21:05.015 --> 00:21:06.266 position:50% align:center
Thank you very much.

00:21:06.349 --> 00:21:08.768 position:50% align:center
I'd be lying if I said
that I had no regrets,

00:21:08.852 --> 00:21:10.812 position:50% align:center
but I'm proud that I've
been able to introduce

00:21:10.895 --> 00:21:12.522 position:50% align:center
a new way of performing
to the sport

00:21:12.605 --> 00:21:14.107 position:50% align:center
of skate-leading.

00:21:14.190 --> 00:21:16.484 position:50% align:center
We've already started getting
ready for next year.

00:21:16.568 --> 00:21:17.652 position:50% align:center
Hope you'll cheer us on!

00:21:17.736 --> 00:21:18.611 position:50% align:center
Thanks for the love!

00:21:18.695 --> 00:21:19.821 position:50% align:center
And we love you back!

00:21:19.904 --> 00:21:20.947 position:50% align:center
From our hearts--

00:21:21.031 --> 00:21:23.116 position:50% align:center
Miá*Leon! Noa!

00:21:24.242 --> 00:21:26.119 position:50% align:center
[MAESHIMA]
Dude, he's on TV again.

00:21:26.202 --> 00:21:28.204 position:50% align:center
Well, the show needs
to wrap things up.

00:21:28.288 --> 00:21:30.248 position:50% align:center
It's almost the end
of this segment.

00:21:30.331 --> 00:21:32.542 position:50% align:center
But this season
isn't over yet, is it?

00:21:32.625 --> 00:21:33.877 position:50% align:center
Right!

00:21:33.960 --> 00:21:35.962 position:50% align:center
And here's some fun,
breaking news for your fans.

00:21:36.046 --> 00:21:39.174 position:50% align:center
Kuonji will now be commentating
for the Grand Prix finals!

00:21:39.257 --> 00:21:40.425 position:50% align:center
Gonna be fun!

00:21:40.508 --> 00:21:41.885 position:50% align:center
What?

00:21:41.968 --> 00:21:43.178 position:50% align:center
[AKIMITSU] Oh, my gosh, do
you think he lost on purpose

00:21:43.261 --> 00:21:44.429 position:50% align:center
so he could do that?

00:21:44.512 --> 00:21:45.930 position:50% align:center
Nah. You kidding?

00:21:46.014 --> 00:21:47.682 position:50% align:center
He would've figured
out some way to do

00:21:47.766 --> 00:21:48.892 position:50% align:center
both simultaneously.

00:21:50.060 --> 00:21:52.771 position:50% align:center
I thought I'd try doing
all three at one time.

00:21:52.854 --> 00:21:54.773 position:50% align:center
Don't you think that'd
be so much cooler?

00:21:54.856 --> 00:21:56.566 position:50% align:center
Maeshima, you called it.

00:21:56.649 --> 00:21:57.942 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
That's uncanny.

00:21:58.026 --> 00:21:59.819 position:50% align:center
Has he already recruited you
for his team next year?

00:21:59.903 --> 00:22:02.447 position:50% align:center
Yeah, right, shut up.

00:22:02.530 --> 00:22:05.116 position:50% align:center
Who knows?
I can't predict the future.

00:23:37.250 --> 00:23:38.585 position:50% align:center
Hey, Shinozaki!

00:23:38.668 --> 00:23:40.378 position:50% align:center
You who shares
my princely title.

00:23:40.462 --> 00:23:41.296 position:50% align:center
[SHINOZAKI]
Your what?

00:23:41.379 --> 00:23:42.422 position:50% align:center
[KUONJI]
I have a proposal.

00:23:42.505 --> 00:23:43.798 position:50% align:center
Wanna hold a birthday
event together?

00:23:43.882 --> 00:23:45.133 position:50% align:center
--[SHINOZAKI] Seriously?
--[KUONJI] I know!

00:23:45.216 --> 00:23:47.177 position:50% align:center
We'll gather ten people
and celebrate every month.

00:23:47.260 --> 00:23:49.262 position:50% align:center
--[SHINOZAKI] That sounds--
--[KUONJI] We're so in sync!

00:23:49.346 --> 00:23:50.472 position:50% align:center
--[SHINOZAKI] Sure.
--[KUONJI] Yay!